{
  "plugin": "hpa-status",
  "version": "v0.9.0",
  "homepage": "https://github.com/mattsu2020/kubectl-hpa-status",
  "description": "Displays detailed HorizontalPodAutoscaler status including current and\ntarget utilization, replica counts, scaling conditions, metric analysis,\nand interpretation of scaling decisions. Features include health scoring,\nKEDA ScaledObject cross-reference, VPA conflict detection, metrics pipeline\ndiagnostics, resource request consistency checks, safe dry-run-first patch\nsuggestions, interactive TUI dashboard, stabilization window countdown,\nstandalone reports, shell completion, and Japanese language support.\nThis plugin reads existing HPA status, metrics, conditions, and events\nto provide human-readable analysis without reimplementing the HPA\ncontroller's internal decision logic.\n",
